.2640699953308553, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before competing at the Olympic Trials, Scott transferred to USC from the University of Virginia after COVID-19 granted him an additional year of NCAA eligibility.\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 798, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"score\": 0.9999951526462315, \"rank\": 4.6225187632027735e-06, \"text\": \"USC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USC_Trojans\"}, {\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9635866849828566, \"rank\": 0.037789035568448974, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.999989784702501, \"rank\": 1.0215400311279423e-05, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Throughout a four-year stint with Virginia, Scott earned several All-American recognitions in both indoor and outdoor triple jump.\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 1032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9548183694512326, \"rank\": 0.04684707595289225, \"text\": \"Virginia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 946, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.7828553447725943, \"rank\": 0.2640699953308553, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 967, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\", \"score\": 0.9999999520582616, \"rank\": 4.793651306228012e-08, \"text\": \"All-American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He holds the Virginia school record in the triple jump at 56-0.5 (17.08m) and the long jump at 25-8.25 (7.83m).\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9548183694512326, \"rank\": 0.04684707595289225, \"text\": \"Virginia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2019, Scott won the NCAA indoor triple jump title at 55-5 (16.89m) followed by a runner-up finish at that year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s NCAA outdoor championships.\\u00c2  Scott has accumulated five Atlantic Coast Conference jump titles with four in the triple jump and one in the long jump, a history-making feat.\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.7828553447725943, \"rank\": 0.2640699953308553, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}, {\"begin\": 1168, \"end\": 1172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.999989784702501, \"rank\": 1.0215400311279423e-05, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"score\": 0.7828553447725943, \"rank\": 0.2640699953308553, \"text\": \"Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Scott\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joined an exclusive group of only five athletes who have won three or more conference triple jump titles in ACC history.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_Coast_Conference\", \"score\": 0.9999999999447482, \"rank\": 5.525318551739493e-11, \"text\": \"ACC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_Coast_Conference\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlantic_Coast_Conference\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris-bound Olympian was the back-to-back USTFCCCA Southeast Region Indoor Field Athlete of the Year in 2019 and 2020, additionally receiving the USTFCCCA Southeast Region Outfield Field Athlete of the Year award in 2019.\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1577, \"end\": 1585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9997969350478856, \"rank\": 0.0002031061957614407, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence